<subSubSection id="F8D66512FF29C126FF25FF6FA7A35866" pageId="3" pageNumber="273" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="B0733699FF29C126FF25FF6FA7A35866" blockId="3.[151,1437,150,1581]" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis id="82B8EA8BFF29C126FF25FF6FA2435AB4" bold="true" box="[199,314,150,176]" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. This new species differs from all other species of the genus by the following combination of characters: Metasoma entirely black; propodeal enclosure apically triangular, only longitudinally carinated inside; mesosoma (except tegula brownish on outer side) entirely black, without ferruginous red markings. This new species come close to 
<taxonomicName id="77CC4D1AFF29C126FED9FEFAA1225B19" authority="Krombein" authorityName="Krombein" authorityYear="1985" box="[315,603,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Alysson" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triangularis">
<emphasis id="82B8EA8BFF29C126FED9FEFAA2985B19" box="[315,481,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">A. triangularis</emphasis>
Krombein
</taxonomicName>
in having metasoma entirely black, propodeal enclosure apically triangularly pointed, and mesosoma (except tegulae brownish on outer side) entirely black, without ferruginous red markings but distinctly differs from 
<taxonomicName id="77CC4D1AFF29C126FE1EFEB2A1DB5B61" authorityName="Krombein" authorityYear="1985" box="[508,674,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Alysson" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="triangularis">
<emphasis id="82B8EA8BFF29C126FE1EFEB2A1DB5B61" box="[508,674,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">A. triangularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having the characters mentioned in the couplet number 5 of the key. As per the key for Chinese species by 
<bibRefCitation id="D45D4B68FF29C126FD96FE96A0375B8D" author="Wu, Y. &amp; Zhou, Q." box="[628,846,367,393]" pageId="3" pageNumber="273" pagination="214 - 222" refId="ref6039" refString="Wu, Y. &amp; Zhou, Q. (1987) A study of the genus Alysson and descriptions of new species from China. Acta Entomologica Sinica, 30, 214 - 222." type="journal article" year="1987">Wu &amp; Zhou (1987)</bibRefCitation>
, this new species comes close to 
<taxonomicName id="77CC4D1AFF29C126FB22FE96A3895BA9" authority="Wu &amp; Zhou" authorityName="Wu &amp; Zhou" authorityYear="1987" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Alysson" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sichuanensis">
<emphasis id="82B8EA8BFF29C126FB22FE96A6175B8D" box="[1216,1390,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">A. sichuanensis</emphasis>
Wu &amp; Zhou
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="77CC4D1AFF29C126FEC5FE6AA1395BA9" authority="Wu &amp; Zhou" authorityName="Wu &amp; Zhou" authorityYear="1987" box="[295,576,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Alysson" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carinatus">
<emphasis id="82B8EA8BFF29C126FEC5FE6AA2C85BA8" box="[295,433,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">A. carinatus</emphasis>
Wu &amp; Zhou
</taxonomicName>
but differs distinctly from both. It differs from 
<taxonomicName id="77CC4D1AFF29C126FBBBFE6AA67E5BA9" authorityName="Wu &amp; Zhou" authorityYear="1987" box="[1113,1287,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Alysson" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sichuanensis">
<emphasis id="82B8EA8BFF29C126FBBBFE6AA67E5BA9" box="[1113,1287,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">A. sichuanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having no creamy white to yellow spot between antennal sockets (in 
<taxonomicName id="77CC4D1AFF29C126FCC9FE4EA0A35BD5" authorityName="Wu &amp; Zhou" authorityYear="1987" box="[811,986,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Alysson" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sichuanensis">
<emphasis id="82B8EA8BFF29C126FCC9FE4EA0A35BD5" box="[811,986,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">A. sichuanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a yellow spot present between antennal sockets) and clypeus with a creamy white to yellow band at apical half only (in 
<taxonomicName id="77CC4D1AFF29C126FBE5FE22A7CC5BF1" authorityName="Wu &amp; Zhou" authorityYear="1987" box="[1031,1205,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Alysson" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sichuanensis">
<emphasis id="82B8EA8BFF29C126FBE5FE22A7CC5BF1" box="[1031,1205,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">A. sichuanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
most part of clypeus yellow except its basal margin and centre black). It differs from 
<taxonomicName id="77CC4D1AFF29C126FC82FE06A090581C" authorityName="Wu &amp; Zhou" authorityYear="1987" box="[864,1001,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Alysson" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carinatus">
<emphasis id="82B8EA8BFF29C126FC82FE06A090581C" box="[864,1001,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">A. carinatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having clypeus with a creamy white to yellow band at apical half (in 
<taxonomicName id="77CC4D1AFF29C126FDE5FDDAA1E95838" authorityName="Wu &amp; Zhou" authorityYear="1987" box="[519,656,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Alysson" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carinatus">
<emphasis id="82B8EA8BFF29C126FDE5FDDAA1E95838" box="[519,656,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">A. carinatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, clypeus with two yellow spots) and second recurrent vein joining to third submarginal cell (in 
<taxonomicName id="77CC4D1AFF29C126FE5BFDBEA13A5864" authorityName="Wu &amp; Zhou" authorityYear="1987" box="[441,579,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Alysson" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="273" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carinatus">
<emphasis id="82B8EA8BFF29C126FE5BFDBEA13A5864" box="[441,579,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">A. carinatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, second recurrent vein joining to second submarginal cell).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F8D66512FF29C126FF25FD93A02A5FE1" pageId="3" pageNumber="273" type="description">
<paragraph id="B0733699FF29C126FF25FD93A6E45F99" blockId="3.[151,1437,150,1581]" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis id="82B8EA8BFF29C126FF25FD93A2205880" bold="true" box="[199,345,618,644]" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">Description.</emphasis>
<typeStatus id="6F77883BFF29C126FEBDFD92A2BE5881" box="[351,455,619,645]" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">Holotype</typeStatus>
female (
<figureCitation id="28F72A1CFF29C126FDC8FD92A1E05881" box="[554,665,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[209,1379,185,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-18@2.[203,1385,179,1918]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Alysson bengalensis sp. nov. Holotype ♀. 1. Habitus, lateral view. 2. Head, frontal view. 3. Lower half of head, frontal view. 4. Antenna. 5. Head and mesosoma, dorsal view. 6. Propodeum, dorsal view. 7. Forewing. 8. Hindwing. 9. Metasoma, dorsal view. 10. Last metasomal tergite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4416255" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4416255/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">Fig. 1–10</figureCitation>
). Length 
<quantity id="77349B7CFF29C126FCE1FD92A0135881" box="[771,874,619,645]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.83" pageId="3" pageNumber="273" unit="mm" value="7.83">7.83 mm</quantity>
; forewing length 
<quantity id="77349B7CFF29C126FBCFFD92A7ED5881" box="[1069,1172,619,645]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.43" pageId="3" pageNumber="273" unit="mm" value="6.43">6.43 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis id="82B8EA8BFF29C126FB7DFD93A78C5881" bold="true" box="[1183,1269,618,645]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">Colour.</emphasis>
Black, the following parts creamy white: mandible except apex, a band at apical half of clypeus (not extending towards lateral margins of clypeus), narrow stripe along inner eye margin and extending halfway to anterior ocellus, scape beneath, fore coxa beneath, narrow streak anteriorly on fore tibia, and pair of round anterolateral spots on Gt 
<subScript id="2C4834DCFF29C126FB0AFD10A78958F3" attach="left" box="[1256,1264,745,759]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">2</subScript>
. The following brown: tarsal segments, and outer sides of tegula. Wings clear except forewing with two infumated bands; outer infumated band covers most of marginal cell, apical third of first submarginal cell, second and third submarginal cells, outer half of third discoidal cell, extending toward posterior margin of wing; inner infumated band covers basal half of first discoidal cell, second discoidal cell almost entirely except apex and apex of submedial cell. Vestiture silvery, subappressed; some longer suberect setae also present on mandible, clypeus, mesopleuron, coxae and femora beneath, sides of Gt 
<subScript id="2C4834DCFF29C126FDE0FC38A16159CB" attach="left" box="[514,536,961,975]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">3-6</subScript>
and Gs 
<subScript id="2C4834DCFF29C126FD92FC38A1FC59CB" attach="left" box="[624,645,961,975]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">2-6</subScript>
; pygidial setae silvery. 
<emphasis id="82B8EA8BFF29C126FC76FC57A0A059CD" bold="true" box="[916,985,942,969]" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis id="82B8EA8BFF29C126FC76FC57A0AB59CD" bold="true" box="[916,978,942,969]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">Head</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Head width 1.98 × interocular distance at antennal insertions and 1.48 × that at anterior ocellus (
<figureCitation id="28F72A1CFF29C126FCF8FC2AA02059E9" box="[794,857,979,1005]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[209,1379,185,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-18@2.[203,1385,179,1918]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Alysson bengalensis sp. nov. Holotype ♀. 1. Habitus, lateral view. 2. Head, frontal view. 3. Lower half of head, frontal view. 4. Antenna. 5. Head and mesosoma, dorsal view. 6. Propodeum, dorsal view. 7. Forewing. 8. Hindwing. 9. Metasoma, dorsal view. 10. Last metasomal tergite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4416255" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4416255/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">Fig 2</figureCitation>
); apical margin of clypeus (
<figureCitation id="28F72A1CFF29C126FB77FC2AA7A859E9" box="[1173,1233,979,1005]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[209,1379,185,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-18@2.[203,1385,179,1918]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Alysson bengalensis sp. nov. Holotype ♀. 1. Habitus, lateral view. 2. Head, frontal view. 3. Lower half of head, frontal view. 4. Antenna. 5. Head and mesosoma, dorsal view. 6. Propodeum, dorsal view. 7. Forewing. 8. Hindwing. 9. Metasoma, dorsal view. 10. Last metasomal tergite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4416255" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4416255/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">Fig 3</figureCitation>
) trilobate, middle lobe larger than lateral lobes; labrum short, about as wide as lobate section of clypeus and with subtruncate apical margin; front with shallow median groove evanescent at upper half of front, with small punctures; OOL 3 × POL (in female 
<typeStatus id="6F77883BFF29C126FEF0FBC6A20B5E5D" box="[274,370,1087,1113]" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">paratype</typeStatus>
OOL 4 × POL); POL 0.36 × ocellooccipital distance. Antenna as in 
<figureCitation id="28F72A1CFF29C126FB99FBC6A7A55E5D" box="[1147,1244,1087,1113]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[209,1379,185,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-18@2.[203,1385,179,1918]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Alysson bengalensis sp. nov. Holotype ♀. 1. Habitus, lateral view. 2. Head, frontal view. 3. Lower half of head, frontal view. 4. Antenna. 5. Head and mesosoma, dorsal view. 6. Propodeum, dorsal view. 7. Forewing. 8. Hindwing. 9. Metasoma, dorsal view. 10. Last metasomal tergite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4416255" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4416255/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">Figure 4</figureCitation>
, length of antennal segments as follows, scape: pedicel: fu 
<subScript id="2C4834DCFF29C126FD94FB8CA1075E87" attach="left" box="[630,638,1141,1155]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">1</subScript>
: fu 
<subScript id="2C4834DCFF29C126FD47FB8CA1D45E87" attach="right" box="[677,685,1141,1155]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">2</subScript>
: fu 
<subScript id="2C4834DCFF29C126FD31FB8CA1A25E87" attach="left" box="[723,731,1141,1155]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">3</subScript>
: fu 
<subScript id="2C4834DCFF29C126FCE0FB8CA0735E87" attach="left" box="[770,778,1141,1155]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">4</subScript>
: fu 
<subScript id="2C4834DCFF29C126FCD3FB8CA0405E87" attach="right" box="[817,825,1141,1155]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">5</subScript>
: fu 
<subScript id="2C4834DCFF29C126FCBDFB8CA01E5E87" attach="left" box="[863,871,1141,1155]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">6</subScript>
: fu 
<subScript id="2C4834DCFF29C126FC6CFB8CA0EF5E87" attach="left" box="[910,918,1141,1155]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">7</subScript>
: fu 
<subScript id="2C4834DCFF29C126FC5FFB8CA0BC5E87" attach="right" box="[957,965,1141,1155]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">8</subScript>
: fu 
<subScript id="2C4834DCFF29C126FC09FB8CA08A5E87" attach="left" box="[1003,1011,1141,1155]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">9</subScript>
: fu 
<subScript id="2C4834DCFF29C126FBF8FB8CA7535E87" attach="left" box="[1050,1066,1141,1155]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">10</subScript>
= 13: 7.7: 14: 13.5: 12.5: 11: 10: 10: 9.5: 9.5: 9: 12.5. 
<emphasis id="82B8EA8BFF29C126FE64FB7EA1785EA5" bold="true" box="[390,513,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">Mesosoma</emphasis>
. Pronotum dorsally with small punctures, mostly separated by about the width of the diameter of a puncture, with a crenulate groove posteriorly (groove narrowed towards middle); lateral surface of pronotum with some strong oblique rugulae on upper half, lower half mostly glabrous anteriorly; mesoscutum with small subcontiguous punctures; mesopleuron with tiny punctures separated by several times the diameter of a puncture. Dorsal side of propodeum (
<figureCitation id="28F72A1CFF29C126FDB3FAEEA1F75F36" box="[593,654,1303,1330]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[209,1379,185,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-18@2.[203,1385,179,1918]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Alysson bengalensis sp. nov. Holotype ♀. 1. Habitus, lateral view. 2. Head, frontal view. 3. Lower half of head, frontal view. 4. Antenna. 5. Head and mesosoma, dorsal view. 6. Propodeum, dorsal view. 7. Forewing. 8. Hindwing. 9. Metasoma, dorsal view. 10. Last metasomal tergite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4416255" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4416255/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">Fig 6</figureCitation>
) with propodeal enclosure apically triangularly pointed, inner side of enclosure only longitudinally carinated, outer side of enclosure with radiating striae from outer margins of enclosure and few rugoso-reticulations towards periphery, lateral tooth well developed; posterior side of propodeum smooth on either sides of its median carina. Forewing (
<figureCitation id="28F72A1CFF29C126FD44FA7AA1935F99" box="[678,746,1411,1437]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[209,1379,185,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-18@2.[203,1385,179,1918]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Alysson bengalensis sp. nov. Holotype ♀. 1. Habitus, lateral view. 2. Head, frontal view. 3. Lower half of head, frontal view. 4. Antenna. 5. Head and mesosoma, dorsal view. 6. Propodeum, dorsal view. 7. Forewing. 8. Hindwing. 9. Metasoma, dorsal view. 10. Last metasomal tergite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4416255" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4416255/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
) with second recurrent vein joins with third submarginal cell.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B0733699FF29C126FF75FA5EA02A5FE1" blockId="3.[151,1437,150,1581]" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">
<emphasis id="82B8EA8BFF29C126FF75FA5EA2765FC5" bold="true" box="[151,271,1447,1473]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">Metasoma</emphasis>
. Gt 
<subScript id="2C4834DCFF29C126FEDBFA40A2385FC3" attach="left" box="[313,321,1465,1479]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">1</subScript>
and Gt 
<subScript id="2C4834DCFF29C126FE72FA40A2E15FC3" attach="left" box="[400,408,1465,1479]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">2</subScript>
almost impunctate except for sparse, scattered setae on sides (
<figureCitation id="28F72A1CFF29C126FBAEFA5EA7F35FC5" box="[1100,1162,1447,1473]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[209,1379,185,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-18@2.[203,1385,179,1918]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–10. Alysson bengalensis sp. nov. Holotype ♀. 1. Habitus, lateral view. 2. Head, frontal view. 3. Lower half of head, frontal view. 4. Antenna. 5. Head and mesosoma, dorsal view. 6. Propodeum, dorsal view. 7. Forewing. 8. Hindwing. 9. Metasoma, dorsal view. 10. Last metasomal tergite." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4416255" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4416255/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">Fig 9</figureCitation>
); base of Gt 
<subScript id="2C4834DCFF29C126FAF0FA40A6635FC3" attach="left" box="[1298,1306,1465,1479]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="273">1</subScript>
with strong longitudinal cavities on either side, margined by strong carina.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F8D66512FF29C126FF25FA16A66D5C0D" box="[199,1300,1519,1545]" pageId="3" pageNumber="273" type="etymology">
